Defendant Rafael Luis Tejeda in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  Defendant Rafael Luis Tejeda in custody.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Statements made as to sentencing by State, Defense and Defendant.  Additional statements by: ALEJANDRO R.

Defendant sentenced to serve NINE (9) MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for FIFTY-TWO (52) DAYS time served.  Huber privileges for work, treatment and school.  Court approved Electronic Monitoring subject to HoC screening.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of FIFTEEN (15) MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:

* Court ordered the defendant to serve SIXTY (60) DAYS in the House of Correction.  FORTHWITH.  Huber privileges for work, treatment and school.  Court approved Electronic Monitoring subject to HoC screening..
* Mental Health Evaluation and take all prescribed medications.
* Medically assisted treatment if appropriate.
* Complete any and all other counselling deemed appropriate.
* Use a physician disclosure form.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol. 
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Obtain GED/HSED.
* Obtain and maintain employment or school.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered WITH TAx Intercept.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

The Court ordered that all court costs, fees, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment WITH tax intercept or other means.

Pursuant to 973.015, Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a class H or I felony or a misdemeanor, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Upon successful completion of the sentence.  Court will grant expungement if defendant successfully completes sentence and has no further violations of the law, upon submission of motion.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Post-conviction Relief;
Ineligible Voting Notice;
Pre-trial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant Rafael Luis Tejeda in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  Defendant Rafael Luis Tejeda in custody.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Hearing proceeded on the Record.  State moved to REVOKE the agreement.  Defense and Defendant conceded that there is a factual basis to REVOKE.  The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of judgment of conviction.  Court will allow a global resolution if this case goes to the Defendant's other matter or vice versa.  Defense advised that it is too early to determine.  DEFENDANT IS REMANDED PENDING THE NEXT DATE.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 12, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
